    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an expert Email Intelligence Analyst.\nAnalyze the email below carefully and extract structured information accurately.\nEmail Details\nSender:\n{{ $json.sender }}\nSubject:\n{{ $json.subject }}\nBody:\n{{ $json.body }}\nReceived:\n{{ $json.received_at }}\nInstructions\n1. Write a concise summary of the email in one or two sentences.\n2. Assign exactly one priority:\n- High\n- Medium\n- Low\n3. Classify the email into exactly one category:\n- Meeting\n- Finance\n- Work\n- Support\n- Marketing\n- Personal\n- Notification\n- Security\n- Other\n4. Set \"\"important\"\" to \"true\" only if the email requires attention or action. Otherwise set it to \"false\".\n5. Extract every actionable task into the \"action_items\" array.\n6. Determine whether the email contains a meeting invitation or meeting schedule.\n- If yes, set \"\"has_meeting\"\" to \"true\".\n- Otherwise, set it to \"false\".\n7. If the email contains a meeting:\n- Extract the meeting date exactly as it appears in the email.\n  \n  - \"Tomorrow\" → \"Tomorrow\"\n  - \"Next Monday\" → \"Next Monday\"\n  - \"June 30, 2026\" → \"June 30, 2026\"\n- Extract the meeting time exactly as written.\n  \n  - \"2:00 PM\"\n  - \"10 AM\"\n  - \"14:30\"\n8. Only return \"null\" for \"meeting_date\" or \"meeting_time\" if the email truly does not mention them.\n9. Base every conclusion only on the email content. Do not invent information.\n10. Assign a confidence score between 0 and 100 reflecting how confident you are in your classification and extraction.\n- 90–100 = Very confident. Email is clear and unambiguous.\n- 70–89 = Confident. Minor ambiguity but conclusion is clear.\n- 50–69 = Uncertain. Email is vague or could fit multiple categories.\n- Below 50 = Very uncertain. Insufficient information to classify reliably.\nOutput Requirements\nReturn ONLY a single valid JSON object.\nDo NOT wrap the JSON in Markdown.\nDo NOT use \"json or \".\nDo NOT include explanations, notes, comments, greetings, or any text before or after the JSON.\nThe response must begin with \"{\" and end with \"}\".\nThe JSON object must contain exactly these fields:\n{\n  \"summary\": \"string\",\n  \"priority\": \"High | Medium | Low\",\n  \"category\": \"Meeting | Finance | Work | Support | Marketing | Personal | Notification | Security | Other\",\n  \"important\": true,\n  \"action_items\": [\n    \"string\"\n  ],\n  \"has_meeting\": false,\n  \"meeting_date\": null,\n  \"meeting_time\": null,\n  \"confidence_score\": 85\n}\nRules:\n- \"summary\" must always be a string.\n- \"priority\" must always be one of: High, Medium, Low.\n- \"category\" must always be one of the listed categories.\n- \"important\" must always be a boolean (\"true\" or \"false\").\n- \"action_items\" must always be an array. If there are no tasks, return an empty array \"[]\".\n- \"has_meeting\" must always be a boolean.\n- \"meeting_date\" must be either the exact text from the email or \"null\".\n- \"meeting_time\" must be either the exact text from the email or \"null\".\n- \"confidence_score\" must always be a number between 0 and 100.",
        "options": {}
      },
